BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 221.52 750 Td (HOW TO DO NATURE STUDY) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 50 740 m 562 740 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 715 Td (Charlotte Mason believed that children learn best through direct) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 700 Td (contact with the natural world. Nature study is not about textbooks -) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 685 Td (it is about stepping outside and truly SEEING what is around you.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 670 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 655 Td (THE PRACTICE IS SIMPLE:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 640 Td (1. Go outside regularly \(aim for weekly, same location if possible\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 625 Td (2. SIT QUIETLY for the first 5 minutes - just observe) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 610 Td (3. Choose ONE thing to study closely \(a leaf, insect, cloud, rock\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 595 Td (4. SKETCH what you see \(skill does not matter - observation does\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 580 Td (5. RECORD details: color, size, texture, behavior, habitat) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 565 Td (6. RESEARCH what you found when you return home) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 550 Td (7. Keep this journal as your growing record of discovery) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 535 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 520 Td (TIPS FOR SUCCESS:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 505 Td (- Bring a magnifying glass to notice small details) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 490 Td (- Go at different times of day \(dawn, midday, dusk\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 475 Td (- Visit the same spot across seasons to notice changes) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 460 Td (- Let your child lead - follow THEIR curiosity) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 445 Td (- There are no wrong observations) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 430 Td (- Silence is part of the practice \(resist filling every moment with talk\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 415 Td (- Bring field guides if you want to identify species) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 400 Td (- A camera can supplement sketching but should not replace it) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 385 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 370 Td (WHAT YOU NEED:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 355 Td (- This journal and a pencil \(colored pencils optional\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 340 Td (- Magnifying glass) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 325 Td (- Comfortable outdoor clothing) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 50 310 Td (- A willing heart to slow down and notice) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
